No fewer than fifteen persons in Ebonyi State have been jailed for drug abuse and trafficking between January and June this year.
They were convicted in various courts across the state according to the state command of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA).
The 15 convicts were among the 141 suspects arrested for drug abuse and trafficking in the state in the last six months.
The state commander of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), Umar Issa Adoro disclosed this at the Federal Government Girls’ College Ezzamgbo Ohaukwu Local Government Area of the State while declaring open the 2019 International Day Against Drug Abuse/Trafficking .
124 of the suspects were males while 17 of them were females, explaining that a total of 93.0971 kg of drugs were seized.
This, he said comprised Cannabis Sativa ( 90.552 KG), Cocaine (0.0103 KG), Psychotropic Substance (1.2674 KG), saying that the Theme of 2019 International Day Against Drug Abuse entitled “Justice For Health, Health For Justice” was selected by the United Nations to tackle the menace of Drugs related problems in the World.
“The campaign is organized for schools because the children are the target, they are the silent victims, they are the ones to be lured in Drug Abuse cases,” he said.